For the third time, Ogun State Governor, Dapo Abiodun, yesterday extended the COVID-19 lockdown in the state for another one week. Abiodun while addressing newsmen his office cited non compliance with safety regulations and community spread of the virus as reasons for the extension. He said state officials would continue to monitor the level of compliance and community transmission in order to determine easing of the lockdown. He extended the lockdown till Sunday, May 24. Dear valued readers, subscribe to the Daily Trust e-paper to continue enjoying our diet of authoritative news. Kindly subscribe here Ogun extends Covid-19 lockdown a third time Ogun extends lockdown, as gov decries non – compliance ‘Extension of lockdown in Ogun insensitive’